🟢 Basic to Advanced
1. Create a Student class with private variables id and name. Use getters and setters to set and print values.
2. Create an Employee class with private variables empId and salary. Access them using getter and setter methods.
3. Create a Car class with private variables brand and price. Set values using setters and display using getters.
4. Create a BankAccount class with private variables accountNo and balance. Use getters and setters to update and display data.
5. Create a Product class with private variables productName and price. Only allow price update if it is greater than 0 (validation in setter).
6. Create a Student class where age is private. In setter, ensure age is not negative before assigning.
7. Create a User class with private variables username and password. Do NOT create a getter for password.
8. Create a Mobile class with private variables brand, model, and price. Use getters and setters to manage data.
9. Create a Rectangle class with private variables length and width. Use setters and calculate area using a method.
10. Create a Customer class with private variables customerId, name, and email. Validate email contains "@" before setting it in setter.